lead_paragraph: SENATE NOMINEES IN CALIFORNIA TO CAMPAIGN AS TEAM SACRAMENTO, Calif., June 8 (AP) -- Dianne Feinstein and Representative Barbara Boxer will campaign for their Senate seats as a team to excite voters and lump together their Republican opponents -- one moderate, one conservative, a top state Democrat says. The Democratic nominees face John Seymour, an interim Senator, and Bruce Herschensohn, respectively.
